'''John Greco''' is an American philosopher. He is the Leonard and Elizabeth Eslick Chair in Philosophy at [[Saint Louis University]]. Greco received his Ph.D. from [[Brown University]] in 1989, where he studied under [[Ernest Sosa]], and his AB from [[Georgetown University]] in 1983.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slu.edu/colleges/AS/philos/site/people/faculty/Greco/|title=John Greco|website=www.slu.edu|access-date=2017-09-27}}</ref> His research interests are in [[epistemology]] and [[metaphysics]] and he has published widely on virtue epistemology, epistemic normativity, skepticism, and Thomas Reid. He is the Editor of [[American Philosophical Quarterly]].<ref>''The Blackwell Guide to Epistemology'' [1999, 2004], back cover.</ref> For 2013-15, together with [[Eleonore Stump]], he holds a $3.3 million grant from the [[John Templeton Foundation]] for a project on intellectual humility.<ref name="humility">{{cite web|title=The Philosophy and Theology of Intellectual humility|url=http://humility.slu.edu|accessdate=2014-04-24}}</ref>
