{{short description|Canadian theologian and academic}} '''Robert M. Doran''' (born 1939) is a Canadian theologian and Emmett Doerr Chair in Catholic Systematic Theology at [[Marquette University]]. He is known for his research on the works of [[Bernard Lonergan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=THE STARTING POINT OF SYSTEMATIC THEOLOGY |url=http://cdn.theologicalstudies.net/67/67.4/67.4.2.pdf |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref>
