{{Notability|date=June 2011}}
'''Throssel Hole Buddhist Abbey''' is a [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] [[monastery]] and retreat centre located in [[Northumberland]], in northern [[England]]. It follows the Serene Reflection [[Meditation]] Tradition, similar to the [[Sōtō]] [[Zen]] sect in [[Japan]]. It is part of the Order of Buddhist Contemplatives.

Throssel Hole was established in 1972.  It offers retreats, festivals and other events for anyone who wishes to learn about or deepen their practice of meditation.

It has been reviewed by the national press.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hansson|first1=Mia|title=Left heartbroken by my ex, I moved to a monastery|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2010/jan/08/first-person-mia-hansson|website=The Guardian|accessdate=16 December 2014}}</ref> and elsewhere.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Throssel Hole Buddhist Abbey, North East England, United Kingdom|url = http://www.worldreviewer.com/travel-guides/alternative/throssel-hole-buddhist-abbey/15250/|website = World Reviewer|accessdate = 2015-10-10|language = en}}</ref>  In 2005 it featured in a BBC article on The History of Buddhism in Britain.<ref>{{Cite web|title = BBC - Religions - Buddhism: History of Buddhism in Britain|url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/religion/religions/buddhism/history/britishbuddhism_1.shtml|accessdate = 2015-10-10}}</ref>

People who have been there share their experiences.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Undeceivable - nature, zen and sliding: Zen is for Idiots - Part 3: Throssel Hole Buddhist Abbey Retreat|url = http://undeceivable.typepad.com/undeceivable/2008/10/zen-is-for-idiots---part-3-throssel-hole-buddhist-abbey-retreat.html|website = undeceivable.typepad.com|accessdate = 2015-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Throssel Hole|url = http://devworkernbo.typepad.com/nbo_development/2006/11/throssel_hole.html|website = Buddhists in Britain|accessdate = 2015-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Herbwormwood's Blog: Staying at Throssel Hole Buddhist Abbey|url = http://herbwormwood.blogspot.co.uk/2015/07/staying-at-throssel-hole-buddhist-abbey.html|website = herbwormwood.blogspot.co.uk|accessdate = 2015-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Rookhope Primary School: Our visit to Throssel Hole Buddhist Monastery|url = http://www.rookhope.durham.sch.uk/gallery/34777|website = www.rookhope.durham.sch.uk|accessdate = 2015-10-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Thole Man: At Throssel Hole Buddhist Abbey|url = http://tholeman.blogspot.co.uk/2005/12/at-throssel-hole-buddhist-abbey.html|website = tholeman.blogspot.co.uk|accessdate = 2015-10-10}}</ref>

